  "chapter": {
    "number": 11,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Zophar Rebukes Job"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Then Zophar the Naamathite replied:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Should this stream of words go unanswered",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and such a speaker be vindicated?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Should your babbling put others to silence?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Will you scoff without rebuke?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have said, ‘My doctrine is sound,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I am pure in Your sight.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But if only God would speak",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and open His lips against you,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "and disclose to you the secrets of wisdom,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for true wisdom has two sides.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Know then that God exacts from you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "less than your iniquity deserves.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Can you fathom the deep things of God",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or discover the limits of the Almighty?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They are higher than the heavens—what can you do?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "They are deeper than Sheol—what can you know?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Their measure is longer than the earth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and wider than the sea.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If He comes along to imprison you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or convenes a court, who can stop Him?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely He knows the deceit of men.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "If He sees iniquity, does He not take note?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But a witless man can no more become wise",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than the colt of a wild donkey can be born a man!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3165
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "As for you, if you direct your heart",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and lift up your hands to Him,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "if you put away the iniquity in your hand,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and allow no injustice to dwell in your tents,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "then indeed you will lift up your face without shame;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you will stand firm and unafraid.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For you will forget your misery,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "recalling it only as waters gone by.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your life will be brighter than noonday;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "its darkness will be like the morning.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will be secure, because there is hope,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and you will look around and lie down in safety.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will lie down without fear,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and many will court your favor.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But the eyes of the wicked will fail,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and escape will elude them;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they will hope for their last breath.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 3165,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or can be born tame",
